        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 7:08PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 707 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
southwest of Hiwasse, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Northwest Arkansas Regional Air...Highfill...
Vaughn...                         Gravette...
Cave Springs...                   Bentonville...
Hiwasse...                        Miller...
Bella Vista...                    Centerton...
Healing Springs...                Decatur...
Lowell...                         Rogers...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 82 and 83.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
